08/01/2007
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- Police seized 400kg of cocaine Sunday (January 7th), the biggest haul to date. The drugs were hidden in 60 barrels that were supposed to contain paint. They were loaded on a truck, intercepted as it entered Macedonia from Kosovo. Police say the high-quality cocaine was produced in Venezuela and had a street value of around 40m euros. The truck's driver, a Macedonian national, was arrested.
In other news, Romanian border police announced Friday that they have smashed an international child trafficking ring, based in the country's southwest. The 15-member network allegedly exploited children, forcing them to steal in Italy. (BBC - 08/01/07; Makfax, Telma TV - 07/01/07; Kathimerini, ANA-MPA - 06/01/07)
